The traditional approach to finding the nth Fibonacci number is to use recursion, which can be slow for large values of n. A more efficient approach is to use an iterative algorithm that calculates the Fibonacci sequence up to the nth number.
However, we can take this a step further and use an unconventional approach that combines the two methods. We can use a recursive function to calculate the Fibonacci sequence up to a certain point, and then switch to an iterative algorithm for the remaining numbers.
