Develop a function in Python that takes two arguments, a base number and an exponent number, and returns the result of the power operation. The function should have a time complexity of O(log n) where n is the exponent number. The function should also handle negative exponents and return a float if necessary.

Additionally, the function should implement its own power algorithm instead of using the built-in power function or any other external libraries. The power algorithm should use a recursive approach to calculate the result, taking advantage of the fact that any number raised to an even exponent can be expressed as the square of that number raised to half the exponent.

