The `rotate` method swaps the length and width of the rectangle.

The `is_golden_rectangle` method calculates the longer and shorter sides of the rectangle, then checks if their ratio is approximately equal to the golden ratio. The check is done by comparing the absolute difference between the ratio and the golden ratio to a small epsilon value.

